1045
01:28:17,516 --> 01:28:20,436
Delay that order!

1046
01:28:33,074 --> 01:28:38,496
Any of you officers or chiefs feel you've
been unjustly caught up in this thing,

1047
01:28:38,621 --> 01:28:41,916
you stand with me now.

1048
01:29:19,954 --> 01:29:23,040
Sir, propulsion has been restored.

1049
01:29:23,124 --> 01:29:25,584
All flooding has been contained.

1050
01:29:27,295 --> 01:29:29,547
All communications are still down.

1051
01:29:35,803 --> 01:29:39,515
Take him away.
Lock him up in the officers' mess.

1052
01:30:16,344 --> 01:30:18,137
Of all the people.

1053
01:30:29,023 --> 01:30:31,943
Weps, return to Missile Control.

1054
01:30:32,026 --> 01:30:33,903
- Mr. Zimmer, stay with me.
- Aye, sir.

1055
01:30:33,986 --> 01:30:39,241
Return to your stations. Inform your men
directly that the captain is in command.

1056
01:30:39,325 --> 01:30:41,661
- I have the conn.
- Captain has the conn.

1057
01:30:41,786 --> 01:30:46,499
- Diving officer, make the depth 1-5-0 feet.
- 1-5-0 feet. Aye, sir.

1058
01:30:46,999 --> 01:30:50,169
- One MC.
- Aye, sir.

1059
01:30:50,252 --> 01:30:54,840
<i>May I have your attention, please.
Crew of the USS Alabama.</i>

1060
01:30:56,175 --> 01:30:59,887
Attempted mutiny has been put down.

1061
01:30:59,971 --> 01:31:05,768
<i>We'll maintain security alert. Authorized
movement only in two-man teams.</i>

1062
01:31:05,851 --> 01:31:08,229
<i>In the absence of
further radio communication,</i>

1063
01:31:08,312 --> 01:31:10,815
<i>on orders from
the National Command Center,</i>

1064
01:31:10,856 --> 01:31:16,153
<i>we'll achieve launch depth as quickly
as we can for strategic missile launch.</i>

1065
01:31:16,237 --> 01:31:18,072
<i>We all know what this means.</i>

1066
01:31:18,197 --> 01:31:21,117
It's not something one would wish for,

1067
01:31:21,200 --> 01:31:25,288
but we have the obligation under
orders issued by our commander in chief

1068
01:31:25,371 --> 01:31:28,249
to prevent the attack on our country.

1069
01:31:28,332 --> 01:31:33,212
<i>Russian missiles will have
launch capability in 15 minutes.</i>

1070
01:31:33,296 --> 01:31:35,298
<i>Set condition One SQ.</i>

1071
01:31:35,381 --> 01:31:41,012
Spin up missiles one through five and
20 through 24 for strategic missile launch.

1072
01:31:41,053 --> 01:31:44,265
The use of nuclear weapons
has been authorized.

1073
01:31:44,348 --> 01:31:48,603
This is the captain.
Mr. Zimmer is the new XO.

1074
01:31:50,563 --> 01:31:53,357
Set condition One SQ.

1075
01:31:56,527 --> 01:32:01,866
Spin up missiles one through five
and 20 through 24 for strategic launch.

1076
01:32:01,907 --> 01:32:04,952
<i>The use of nuclear weapons
has been authorized.</i>

1077
01:32:05,036 --> 01:32:06,412
<i>This is the XO.</i>

1078
01:32:07,830 --> 01:32:09,332
Weapons, Conn.

1079
01:32:09,415 --> 01:32:14,670
Confirm target package SLBM 64741/2

1080
01:32:14,754 --> 01:32:17,632
for missiles one through five
and 20 through 24.

1081
01:32:17,715 --> 01:32:22,178
<i>- Target package confirmation, sir.
- This is the captain.</i>

1082
01:32:30,394 --> 01:32:36,067
Conn, Weapons.
Confirm target package SLBM 64741/2

1083
01:32:36,150 --> 01:32:40,279
for missiles one through five
and 20 through 24. Aye, sir.

1084
01:32:49,914 --> 01:32:52,625
Look, It's not a mutiny.
I did everything by the book.

1085
01:32:52,708 --> 01:32:55,086
It's not about the book.

1086
01:32:55,169 --> 01:32:58,714
If the Russians are gonna launch
and we sit here and do nothing,

1087
01:32:58,756 --> 01:33:00,341
who's gonna stop 'em?

1088
01:33:00,424 --> 01:33:05,054
Half of me is glad the captain came back.
He could be right, you know.

1089
01:33:05,096 --> 01:33:07,598
No orders are valid, Cob,
if they're wrong.

1090
01:33:07,682 --> 01:33:11,102
- We don't know if they're wrong.
- That's true. We don't know.

1091
01:33:11,143 --> 01:33:14,063
That's why we have to find out first.

1092
01:33:20,945 --> 01:33:24,532
What if Radchenko surrendered
and it's over? Hm?

1093
01:33:24,615 --> 01:33:26,575
We launch. They see us.

1094
01:33:26,659 --> 01:33:29,870
They launch.

1095
01:33:29,954 --> 01:33:32,748
Our birds pass each other
in the air. Boom!

1096
01:33:32,832 --> 01:33:35,584
- What do you got?
- Nuclear war.

1097
01:33:35,626 --> 01:33:38,129
Nuclear holocaust.

1098
01:33:44,302 --> 01:33:47,513
I gotta take a wiz.

1099
01:33:49,932 --> 01:33:52,143
OK.

1100
01:33:52,226 --> 01:33:54,020
Sir?

1101
01:34:07,825 --> 01:34:10,578
- What are you doing here?
- Just going to the bath...

1102
01:34:10,661 --> 01:34:12,622
Nobody moves alone.
You know the drill.

1103
01:34:12,663 --> 01:34:15,082
Come on, I need an escort to take a shit?

1104
01:34:15,166 --> 01:34:16,959
Shut up.

1105
01:34:17,001 --> 01:34:19,962
- I'm gonna call Control. You stay there.
- Fuck that.

1106
01:34:20,046 --> 01:34:22,298
I mean it, man.

1107
01:34:26,844 --> 01:34:29,305
OK, Moebius, open the door.

1108
01:34:29,347 --> 01:34:32,683
- You broke my nose, man.
- Shut up, fat boy.

1109
01:34:35,561 --> 01:34:38,230
- Mr. Rivetti, I'm impressed.
- I never liked him.

1110
01:34:38,314 --> 01:34:41,275
Go to Laundry.
Get four sets of coveralls, and four caps.

1111
01:34:41,317 --> 01:34:42,985
Aye, sir.

1112
01:34:43,069 --> 01:34:45,154
Just relax.

1113
01:34:49,492 --> 01:34:52,912
Davis. Can I talk to you a second?

1114
01:34:52,995 --> 01:34:55,331
Come on.

1115
01:34:56,332 --> 01:34:58,834
- Everybody ready?
- Let's do it.

1116
01:35:08,594 --> 01:35:12,223
- We're with you, sir.
- Let's go.

1117
01:35:21,774 --> 01:35:25,194
- Approaching launch depth.
- Very well.

1118
01:35:25,278 --> 01:35:28,406
Make your depth 1-5-0 feet.

1119
01:35:28,489 --> 01:35:32,285
- Zero bubble. Commence hovering.
- Aye, sir.

1120
01:35:32,368 --> 01:35:35,413
Conn, Weapons. Estimated time
to weapons system One SQ,

1121
01:35:35,496 --> 01:35:38,666
three minutes, 30 seconds, sir.

1122
01:35:38,708 --> 01:35:43,462
Conn, Weapons. Russian missiles
will have launch capability in 12 minutes.

1123
01:35:43,546 --> 01:35:45,172
<i>Opening missile hatches.</i>

1124
01:36:02,898 --> 01:36:04,942
<i>- Weps.
- Weps.</i>

1125
01:36:05,026 --> 01:36:07,903
<i>- This is Hunter. Listen to me.
- Where are you?</i>

1126
01:36:07,987 --> 01:36:12,366
Don't worry about that. You can't proceed.
We got other ships that can handle this.

1127
01:36:12,408 --> 01:36:17,038
You can't be influenced by the captain or
anybody else. Make up your own mind.

1128
01:36:17,121 --> 01:36:21,459
Conn, Weapons. Estimated time to
missile launch three minutes and counting.

1129
01:36:21,542 --> 01:36:23,544
Weps, Weps, listen.
Don't do this.

1130
01:36:23,669 --> 01:36:26,589
<i>Once you launch, they cannot come back,</i>

1131
01:36:26,672 --> 01:36:29,634
<i>and you know the repercussions
if we're wrong, Weps.</i>

1132
01:36:29,717 --> 01:36:34,263
If we fire now, we'll be firing while we're
blind and crippled. You understand me?

1133
01:36:34,347 --> 01:36:37,767
<i>- Where the fuck are you?
- Do not remove that firing trigger.</i>

1134
01:36:37,850 --> 01:36:39,769
<i>Do not open the safe.
It's up to you.</i>

1135
01:36:39,852 --> 01:36:43,481
You're the only one that knows
the combination. It's up to you, Weps.

1136
01:36:43,564 --> 01:36:45,566
It's up to you.

1137
01:36:48,152 --> 01:36:50,571
Mind your fuckin' panel!

1138
01:36:57,161 --> 01:37:00,081
- You guys ready?
- Just about, sir.

1139
01:37:03,167 --> 01:37:04,961
Radio, XO. Vossler?

1140
01:37:05,044 --> 01:37:09,006
XO, Radio. Sir...
I don't know, sir.

1141
01:37:09,090 --> 01:37:12,551
Vossler, calm down.
Take a deep breath. Are you calm?

1142
01:37:12,635 --> 01:37:13,803
Yeah, sort of.

1143
01:37:13,886 --> 01:37:17,306
Get the radio fixed, Vossler.
How long is it gonna take you?

1144
01:37:17,390 --> 01:37:19,600
I don't know.

1145
01:37:20,643 --> 01:37:23,062
Well, how much time do you need?

1146
01:37:25,273 --> 01:37:26,399
Shit!

1147
01:37:26,482 --> 01:37:28,943
